s to be quickly tested, making issues easy to catch and fix. TFS source control takes CI a step further and implements an expanded version, called Gated Check-in. Gated Check-in attempts a build when changes are checked in;┬áif the build fails, the check-in is rejected. This protects your repository by not allowing changes to be committed if the build fails.\r\n\r\nBelow are the configuration options for CI and Gated Check-in. You specify the directory in source control (or branch, if using Git) for changes:\r\n\r\n<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" src=\"https://confluence/download/attachments/66694463/image2017-7-7%2011%3A32%3A32.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1499796875000&amp;api=v2\" height=\"250\" data-image-src=\"/download/attachments/66694463/image2017-7-7%2011%3A32%3A32.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1499796875000&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"66694455\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"image2017-7-7 11:32:32.png\" data-base-url=\"https://confluence\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"66694463\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"13\" /></span>\r\n<h2 id=\"TeamFoundationServer:ASolutionforContinuousIntegrationandDeployment-Testing\">Testing</h2>\r\nAnother way to protect your repository is to implement automated testing during the build process. TFS provides many modules for running automated tests, and┬áthey work with many testing platforms. You can run multiple types of tests such as unit, functional, and┬áuser interface┬á(e.g., CodedUI and Selenium). TFS can also interpret and give visual analysis of testing metrics such as test success rate,┬ácode coverage, and test run-time. You can also integrate static code analysis tools such as Sonar.\r\n\r\n<em>Below is the screen where you can configure a testing module. This example is the built-in Visual Studio Test module:</em>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" src=\"https://confluence/download/attachments/66694463/image2017-7-7%2016%3A41%3A42.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1499796875000&amp;api=v2\" height=\"400\" data-image-src=\"/download/attachments/66694463/image2017-7-7%2016%3A41%3A42.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1499796875000&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"66694456\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"image2017-7-7 16:41:42.png\" data-base-url=\"https://confluence\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"66694463\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"13\" /></span>\r\n\r\n<em>These are results of an example test run:</em>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" src=\"https://confluence/download/attachments/66694463/image2017-7-7%2016%3A42%3A27.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1499796875000&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"/download/attachments/66694463/image2017-7-7%2016%3A42%3A27.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1499796875000&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"66694457\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"image2017-7-7 16:42:27.png\" data-base-url=\"https://confluence\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"66694463\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"13\" /></span>\r\n<h2 id=\"TeamFoundationServer:ASolutionforContinuousIntegrationandDeployment-ContinuousDeployment\">Continuous Deployment</h2>\r\nOur build system supports a key component of CD, the ability to automatically push your build to your